#: traces/templates-light/traces/about.html:81
msgid "About Biketory"
msgstr "À propos de Biketory"

#: traces/templates-light/traces/about.html:84
msgid ""
"Biketory is a web application that allows cyclists to import their GPX "
"traces\n"
"  and visualise the closed geographic surfaces covered on an interactive map."
msgstr ""
"Biketory est une application web qui permet aux cyclistes d'importer leurs "
"traces GPX\n"
"  et de visualiser les surfaces géographiques fermées parcourues sur une "
"carte interactive."

#: traces/templates-light/traces/about.html:88
msgid "How it works"
msgstr "Comment ça marche"

#: traces/templates-light/traces/about.html:91
msgid ""
"Upload your GPX files, and Biketory automatically detects closed loops\n"
"  in your routes. These surfaces are then displayed on a map and divided\n"
"  into hexagons to track your progress."
msgstr ""
"Téléversez vos fichiers GPX, et Biketory détecte automatiquement les boucles "
"fermées\n"
"  dans vos parcours. Ces surfaces sont ensuite affichées sur une carte et "
"divisées\n"
"  en hexagones pour suivre votre progression."

#: traces/templates-light/traces/about.html:99
msgid ""
"The map is divided into hexagons. Each time one of your rides crosses\n"
"  a hexagon, it becomes <strong>acquired</strong> and your score on that "
"hexagon increases."
msgstr ""
"La carte est divisée en hexagones. Chaque fois qu'un de vos parcours "
"traverse\n"
"  un hexagone, il devient <strong>acquis</strong> et votre score sur cet "
"hexagone augmente."

#: traces/templates-light/traces/about.html:104
msgid ""
"When your score on a hexagon is the highest among all users,\n"
"  that hexagon becomes <strong>conquered</strong>. Other riders can take it "
"back\n"
"  by riding through it more times than you — so keep pedalling!"
msgstr ""
"Lorsque votre score sur un hexagone est le plus élevé parmi tous les "
"utilisateurs,\n"
"  cet hexagone devient <strong>conquis</strong>. D'autres cyclistes peuvent "
"le reprendre\n"
"  en y passant plus de fois que vous — alors continuez à pédaler !"

#: traces/templates-light/traces/about.html:109
msgid "The story"
msgstr "L'histoire"

#: traces/templates-light/traces/about.html:112
msgid ""
"Biketory was born from the passion of a cycling enthusiast who never tires\n"
"  of exploring new gravel paths. Setting off on an adventure, discovering "
"an\n"
"  unknown trail, riding for the sheer joy of riding — that is the spirit of "
"the project.\n"
"  The idea was simple: have a fun way to visualise all the ground\n"
"  covered over your rides, and turn each loop into a small victory\n"
"  on the map."
msgstr ""
"Biketory est né de la passion d'un cycliste qui ne se lasse jamais\n"
"  d'explorer de nouveaux chemins de gravel. Partir à l'aventure, découvrir "
"un\n"
"  sentier inconnu, rouler pour le simple plaisir de rouler — voilà l'esprit "
"du projet.\n"
"  L'idée était simple : avoir un moyen ludique de visualiser tout le "
"terrain\n"
"  parcouru au fil de ses sorties, et transformer chaque boucle en une petite "
"victoire\n"
"  sur la carte."

#: traces/templates-light/traces/about.html:120
msgid "Source code"
msgstr "Code source"

#: traces/templates-light/traces/about.html:123
msgid ""
"Biketory is an open source project. The code is available on\n"
"  <a href=\"https://github.com/rodo/biketory\">GitHub</a>."
msgstr ""
"Biketory est un projet open source. Le code est disponible sur\n"
"  <a href=\"https://github.com/rodo/biketory\">GitHub</a>."

